      • addAfter

        public boolean addAfter(int index,
                        E expectedPriorValue,
                        E addition)
        Description copied from interface: ConcurrentList
        Adds the given value at the given index, after the given value. This atomically adds the value at the given index but only if its predecessor would match the given value.

        The given index will be the index of the newly added item. Any items at that index or after will be shifted by one. The expected prior value is compared against the item at index - 1 and the operation is aborted if the actual value doesn't match.

        Specified by:
        addAfter in interface ConcurrentList<E>
        Parameters:
        index - the index of the newly added item
        expectedPriorValue - the expected value of the new element's predecessor
        addition - the value to add at the given index
        Returns:
        true if the value was added or false if the element's predecessor differed from the expected value

      • addBefore

        public boolean addBefore(int index,
                         E expectedNextValue,
                         E addition)
        Description copied from interface: ConcurrentList
        Adds the given value at the given index, before the given value. This atomically adds the value at the given index but only if its successor would match the given value.

        The given index will be the index of the newly added item. Any items at that index or after will be shifted by one. The expected next value is compared against the item already at the given index (which will be shifted to index + 1 after the operation completes). The operation is aborted if the actual value doesn't match.

        Specified by:

        Parameters:

        expectedNextValue - the expected value of the new element's successor
        addition - the value to add at the given index
        Returns:
        true if the value was added or false if the element's succcessor differed from the expected value

      • subList

        public ConcurrentList<E> subList(int fromIndex,
                                 int toIndex)
        Description copied from interface: ConcurrentList
        Returns a view of the portion of this list between the specified indices. Changes to this list are visible through the returned view, and vice versa.

        The returned list is also a concurrent list. Structural changes made to the underlying list can impact the returned list. For example, if an element is added in the given index range in the underlying list, it will effectively displace the last element of the sub-list (since that last item has now been pushed beyond the end of the index range). Similarly, removing an element in the given index range from the underlying list will cause the sub-list to get a new last element (the item that was after the given range that has now been pulled into the range due to an element removal).

        The returned sub-list should never throw ConcurrentModificationException from any of its operations (although its iterators may throw this exception if concurrent modifications conflict with attempts to modify the list via the iterator).

        Specified by:
        subList in interface ConcurrentList<E>
        Specified by:
        subList in interface java.util.List<E>
